To make the pico de gallo: Dice tomatoes, red onions, jalapeno peppers, garlic and cilantro. Add juice of one lime. To make the guacamole: Smash up avocados. Add some of the pico de gallo. Add salt to taste. Then take a tortilla, add a layer of refried beans, a layer of chili and a layer of cheese. Cover with an additional tortilla and heat in a frying pan. Once toasted, serve with sour cream, pico de gallo and guacamole on the side.